SUMMARY:after work bike ride on the ATT 
DESCRIPTION:Triangle Hiking and Outdoors Group\nWe'll be starting near Sou
 thpoint and final starting point will be sent out Monday evening.\n\nMake 
 sure that your bike is in good working order - tires hold air and are up t
 o pressure\, brakes and shifters work and your chain has been oiled.\n\nWe
 'll be riding about 1 1/2 hour and about 18 miles. The ride is fairly flat
  and shaded and our pace will be moderate (about 12 mph average). I recomm
 end a hard tail or hybrid bike\, but if you really want to bring a road bi
 ke it's ok\, though you'll likely be a bit bored. Unicycles....?\n\nI'll b
 e eating after the ride at a restaurant. You're welcome to join me if you 
 like.\n\nHelmets are required and by signing up you agree to THOG liabilit
 y waiver statement.\n\nPlease Note!! Any cancellation less than 30 hours b
 efore the beginning of the event will be considered a "no show"
