SUMMARY:(Maine) Acadia Nat’l Park/Partial Solar Eclipse/Perseids Meteor 
 Shower
DESCRIPTION:Triangle Hiking and Outdoors Group\n**Updated information belo
 w as of 3/12/26**\n\nCome and be a part of one of THOG’s most ambitious 
 trips. This summer adventure in Maine includes Acadia National Park and Ba
 r Harbor\, as well as two amazing celestial events- A partial Solar Eclips
 e and the Perseids Meteor Shower.\nThis exciting road trip event will be s
 lightly different from other THOG events. We will be partnering with Wande
 rful Journeys\, a local travel club that hosts trips to various destinatio
 ns. I decided to team up with them so it would provide us with another lay
 er of resources for planning\, as well as to enhance the trip experience.\
 n**See RSVP requirements below before you register**.\n\n**Highlights of o
 ur weeklong trip will include:**\n-Hikes in Acadia National Park such as P
 recipice Trail and Beehive Trail\n-Thunder Hole\n-Jordan Pond\n-Maine Lobs
 ter :)\n-Lighthouses in Maine\n-Viewing the partial Solar Eclipse\n-Watchi
 ng the Perseids Meteor Shower (up to 100 per hour this year)\n-Exploring B
 ar Harbor\n-Bar Island Trail hike- a trail that appears only during low ti
 de\n-Exclusive Swag options for trip participants\n\n**Here is a brief ove
 rview of our itinerary on this trip** which is subject to change depending
  on weather and/or other factors:\n8/9- Carpools will meet in a central lo
 cation in the Triangle and begin Day 1 of our trip with an overnight stop 
 at a hotel in NJ\n8/10- Continue our trip with a featured stop along the w
 ay at Portland Head Light then arrive at Acadia Nat'l Park/Bar Harbor for 
 either camping or hotel stay\n8/11- Sunrise at Cadillac Mountain\, hiking 
 choices in Acadia and other activities then dinner at camp or in Bar Harbo
 r\n8/12- **Solar Eclipse/Perseids Meteor Shower Day Activities:** *Watch p
 artial Solar Eclipse* near Otter Point\, Explore Bar Harbor\, *Late-night*
  *viewing of Perseids Meteor Shower* near campground at the coast\n8/13- A
 ctivities: Sunrise and hike at Otter Point\, Bar Island Trail hike\, Thund
 er Hole\, Jordan Pond\, Sunset at Bass Harbor Head Light Station\n8/14- He
 ad back to NJ to our hotel with a featured stop along the way.\n8/15- Cont
 inue our trip back home with a featured stop along the way.\nAll participa
 nts will be required to pay a $100 deposit to secure their spot on this tr
 ip.\n**Accommodations overview:** Everyone will be staying at a designated
  hotel in NJ going to Maine and returning from Maine.\nIn Maine\, you will
  have two stay options:\n-designated Group Campsites (4 nights) that has m
 odern bathrooms\; paid showers are located nearby\n-designated hotel in Ba
 r Harbor (4 nights) two beds per room\nIf you choose the hotel stay in Mai
 ne\, it is crucial that you submit your deposit as soon as you RSVP (see r
 svp requirements below) to secure your hotel spot due to limited room avai
 lability. Roommate info/rules will also be in a link that will be sent to 
 all who RSVP.\n**Estimated Costs:**\nThe costs below include transportatio
 n (gas\, tolls\, parking)\, National Park passes\, Hotel stays during trav
 el\nCamping- $600-$650 per person\nHotel- $1\,100-$1\,150 per person\nThes
 e best estimates may change depending on the number of attendees and could
  decrease or increase. We will notify you of any changes.\n\n**important R
 SVP requirements:**\n\n1. You will be asked a three-part question as you a
 re RSVPing for this event. Please answer completely!\n2. After you RSVP to
  this trip\, you will be sent a **link to your email** **address** that wi
 ll have questions you need to answer as well as a link to pay your **$100 
 deposit (required for every trip participant)**. Links will have all the i
 nformation about the trip\, total costs per person\, rules on how the depo
 sit works\, itinerary\, trip expectations\, and swag information.\nYour sp
 ot on this trip will not be guaranteed until the deposit is paid.\n\nTRIP 
 PARTICIPANT WAIVER OF LIABILITY I fully realize that this activity involve
 s a risk of personal injury\, property damage\, or loss of my person or pr
 operty. I hereby for myself\, my heirs\, executors and administrators\, an
 d same for persons with whom are in my party\, waive and release any claim
 s or rights against Triangle Hiking & Outdoors Group (THOG)\, all of its o
 wners and coordinators for any and all injury\, damages or loss to my pers
 on or property incurred during this activity. I also understand that THOG 
 organizers are not required\, nor should it be assumed that they are CPR/F
 irst Aid/Wilderness Survival Certified and I am responsible for my own per
 sonal safety.\n\nWe look forward to having you be a part of this adventure
 !\nIf you have any questions\, please send me (Larredo) a meetup message o
 r comment below if it is something that could benefit the group. Thanks!\n
 See you all soon!\nLarredo and Geniece
